MEMORY MAP — Version 1.0 Line‑Drawing Engine
Subsystem Variables: d06010 – d063a2

1. High‑Level Layout

	Code

	d06010 – d0602F   Pixel mask table + Bresenham working registers
	d06030 – d0603F   Coordinate registers, latch, and scratch
	d063A0 – d063AF   Mode flags and dispatcher control

	This subsystem uses global variables only — no stack frames, no local allocations.

⭐ 2. Pixel Mask Table (Used by s7)

	d06010 – d0601F : Pixel Mask Table (32 bytes)
	Used to mask bits before OR‑ing in the new pixel value.

	Address Range	Name	Size	Description
	d06010–d0601F	d06010[]	32 bytes	4‑entry repeating mask table used by 
					s7() to merge pixel bits.

	Usage:

	Code

	mask = d06010[si & 0x03]

⭐ 3. Bresenham Working Registers (Used by s9)

	These variables store the deltas, step increments, and error terms for the 
	rasterizer.

	Address	Name	Description
	d06020	StepY_major	Step for Y when X is dominant
	d06022	StepX_major	Step for X when X is dominant
	d06024	LoopCount	Number of pixels to draw
	d06026	DeltaY	Absolute value of dy
	d06028	StepX_minor	Step for X when Y is dominant
	d0602A	StepY_minor	Step for Y when Y is dominant
	d0602C	ErrorStep_minor	Error increment for minor axis
	d0602E	ErrorStep_major	Error increment for major axis

	Functional Summary

	d06020 / d06022 → increments when bx ≥ 0

	d06028 / d0602A → increments when bx < 0

	d0602C / d0602E → error term adjustments

	d06024 → loop counter for s9

⭐ 4. Coordinate Registers (Used by s8 and s9)

	These represent the start and end points of the line.

	Address	Name	Description
	d06035	X1	Starting X coordinate
	d06037	Y1	Starting Y coordinate
	d06039	X2	Ending X coordinate
	d0603B	Y2	Ending Y coordinate

	Used by:

	s8() modifies these across four passes

	s9() reads them to compute dx/dy

⭐ 5. Pixel Latch / Attribute Register

	Address	Name	Description
	d0603D	PixelAttribute	Passed into s7() via DX → AH

	This value becomes the pixel color/bit pattern merged into the framebuffer.

⭐ 6. Mode and Dispatcher Control

	Address	Name	Description
	d063A2	Mode	Controls s8 behavior: skip, fast‑path, or 4‑pass mode

	Mode Values

	Value	Meaning
	0x00	Fast‑path (b067e1)
	0x01	Normal 4‑pass rendering
	0x02	Skip rendering

⭐ 7. Execution Flow Memory Dependencies

	s8() uses:
	d063A2 (mode)

	d06035, d06037, d06039, d0603B (coordinates)

	Writes back modified coordinates for each pass

	s9() uses:
	d06035, d06037, d06039, d0603B (dx/dy)

	d06020–d0602E (Bresenham state)

	d06024 (loop count)

	d0603D (pixel attribute)

	s7() uses:
	si, di (pixel coordinates)

	d06010[] (mask table)

	AH (pixel value)

	ES:[offset] (framebuffer)

